\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs28 Time of Asr:\par
\b0\fs22 The time for Asr begins when the time for Dhuhr ends, i.e., when the length of an object\rquote s shadow becomes equal to the length of the object itself; according to the view of the majority.\par
Abu Hanifah (may Allah have mercy on him) is of the view that Asr begins when the length of an object\rquote s shadow becomes twice the length of the object itself.\par
For the end of the time for Asr, there are two times:\par

\pard 
{\pntext\f0 1.\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec{\pntxta.}}
\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The preferred time: this lasts from the beginning of the time for \lquote Asr until the sun begins to turn yellow.\par
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}The time of necessity. This lasts from the time the sun turns yellow until sunset.\par

