\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs28 Time of Maghrib:\par
\b0\fs22 The time for Maghrib starts immediately after the time for Asr ends, which is when the sun sets, until the twilight or red afterglow has faded. When the red afterglow has disappeared from the sky, the time for Maghrib ends and the time for \lquote Isha\rquote  begins.\par

