\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs28 Time of Isha:\par
\b0\fs22 The time for Isha begins immediately after the time for Maghrib ends (i.e., when the red afterglow disappears from the sky) until midnight, after which is a time of necessity.\par

\pard\sl276\slmult1\qc !!IMG#red_twilight.jpg\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc\fs20 The time of Isha begins when the twilight disappear\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\fs22 To calculate when midnight is, we can calculate the time between sunset and the break of true dawn (when Fajr begins) then we divide it in half; that halfway point is the end of the time for praying Isha (and that is midnight).\par
